      explanation: `## Poison Ivy, Oak, and Sumac

These plants cause an itchy, blistering rash in most people who touch them.

## How to Identify
- "Leaves of three, let it be" (poison ivy and oak)
- Poison sumac has 7-13 leaflets
- All parts of the plant are toxic
- Toxic in all seasons

## What Happens When You Touch It
- Oil called urushiol gets on your skin
- Rash appears 12-72 hours later
- Itchy red bumps and blisters
- Can last 1-3 weeks

## Treatment
- Wash skin with soap and water immediately
- Wash clothes that touched the plant
- Calamine lotion for itching
- Antihistamines may help
- See doctor for severe cases

## Prevention
- Learn to identify the plants
- Wear long sleeves and pants in wooded areas
- Wash skin right away if you touch a plant`,
      keyTerms: [
