      explanation: `## Molecular Mechanisms

### Urushiol Chemistry
- 3-n-pentadecylcatechol and variants
- C15-17 alkenyl side chains
- Oxidation essential for hapten formation
- Electrophilic quinone reacts with nucleophilic proteins

### Immunologic Specificity
- HLA-dependent T-cell recognition
- CD4+ Th1 and Th17 predominate
- CD8+ cytotoxic T cells contribute
- Regulatory T cells modulate response
- Memory T cells persist years

### Cytokine Network
- IFN-γ: Th1 signature
- IL-17: Th17 involvement
- TNF-α: inflammation amplification
- IL-22: keratinocyte effects

## Evidence Base

### Prevention
- Bentoquatam (organoclay barrier): ~68% effective
- Ivy Block\u00ae before exposure
- Potential for oral tolerance induction (experimental)

### Treatment Outcomes
| Intervention | Evidence |
|--------------|----------|
| Early wash (<15min) | Prevents rash |
| Topical steroids | Mild disease only |
| Systemic steroids | Effective, duration critical |
| Antihistamines | Minimal benefit |

### Steroid Duration Studies
- 5-day course: 25% rebound
- 14-day taper: <5% rebound
- 21-day taper: minimal rebound

## Special Considerations

### Cross-Reactivity
- Mango (fruit skin)
- Cashew nut shell
- Japanese lacquer tree
- Ginkgo fruit

### Systemic Contact Dermatitis
- Ingestion of cross-reactive foods
- Widespread dermatitis
- Consider in unexplained flares

### Occupational Exposure
- Forestry workers
- Firefighters (smoke exposure)
- Landscapers
- Prevention and education critical`,
